=Introduction=
Trains are probably the most interesting, and certainly the most common method of transport in OpenTTD.  They are fast and have a high capacity, and are relatively cheap to run.  Most of the engines in OpenTTD are based on real-life equivalents, just like they were in Transport Tycoon and the Deluxe version.  Unfortunately, they retain the mysterious made-up names that came in with Transport Tycoon Deluxe. However, it is possible to change the names to the original, via the 'game options' box - under 'language'

